<p>The <code>@odd</code> property returns TRUE if the current occurrence number is odd.</p>

<h2>Alternate Styling</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  &lt;tr style="{open}@odd ? background:#f0f0f0{close}"&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result:</p>
<table border="1">
  <tr><th>Name</th></tr>
{users}
  <tr style="{@odd ? background:#f0f0f0}">
    <td>{$name}</td>
  </tr>
{/users}
</table>

<h2>Odd Items Only</h2>
<pre>{open}colors{close}
  {open}@odd{close}
    &lt;li&gt;{open}@current{close}. {open}$colors{close}&lt;/li&gt;
  {open}/@odd{close}
{open}/colors{close}</pre>

<p>Result (only odd positions):</p>
<ul>
{colors}
  {@odd}
    <li>{@current}. {$colors}</li>
  {/@odd}
{/colors}
</ul>
